    <para id="import-auto-id1169737805693">Perhaps the easiest way to find magnetic field strength, now that the electric field strength is known, is to use the relationship given by</para>
    <equation id="eip-388"><m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>B</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:msub><m:mi>E</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mi>c</m:mi></m:mfrac><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{B rSub { size 8{0} } = {  {E rSub { size 8{0} } }  over  {c} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math></equation><para id="import-auto-id1169738011409">Entering known values gives</para>
