        <exercise id="fs-id1169737728543" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1169737828373">    <para id="import-auto-id1169737806873">Find the intensity of an electromagnetic wave having a peak magnetic field strength of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>4</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mtext>00</m:mtext><m:mi>×</m:mi><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>9</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msup><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext> T</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{4 "." "00"´"10" rSup { size 8{-9} } " T"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>.</para></problem></exercise>
        <exercise id="fs-id1169737768545" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1169737784899">
<para id="import-auto-id1169737770818">Assume the helium-neon lasers commonly used in student physics laboratories have power outputs of 0.250 mW. (a) If such a laser beam is projected onto a circular spot 1.00 mm in diameter, what is its intensity? (b) Find the peak magnetic field strength. (c) Find the peak electric field strength.</para></problem>
